[thinking] I'm thinking about how dynamic access is generated by tracing agents, which record metadata during method invocation, regardless of any failures. It seems we need the invocation to succeed to consider it fully covered. Now, how can I make `UIManager.createLookAndFeel("Mac OS X")` succeed even on non-Mac systems? One idea is to install a `LookAndFeelInfo` with the name "Mac OS X" and link it to our custom `BasicLookAndFeel`.
[thinking] 
[assistant-event] thinking_end
